Description: Antiquités Egyptiennes, study for Plate 100 of the artist's 'Voyage dans la Basse et la Haute Egypte, pendant les campagnes du Général Bonaparte', 1802; two ornate dishes, one decorated with the heads of two gods (?) Pen and grey ink, with grey wash, touched with white (partly discoloured)
Producer name: Drawn by: Baron Dominique Vivant Denon
Curator's comments: Engraved by Gounot. There is no drawing for the lower images in Plate 100. There is no copy of Denon's 'Voyage...' in the Department. The B.L. copy is at 458.h.12. The minutes of the Trustees' meeting on 12th December, 1835, record that "two or three" of the drawings were missing when the group was offered to the Museum.
Exhibition history: 1999/2000 Oct-Jan, Paris, Musée du Louvre, Denon 1747-1825
Associated names: Associated with: Napoléon I, Emperor of the French (Napoleon)
Illustration to: Baron Dominique Vivant Denon
Associated titles: Voyage dans la Basse et la Haute Egypte
